#: 1801
msgid ""
"This squat old woman looks like she has had all the color bled out of her -- "
"everything from her hair, to her shawl, to her robe - all are shades of "
"gray. The only splotches of color on her come from several strange herbs, "
"which are tied to her belt by their stalks. The herbs make a strange "
"*swsshhh* when she moves, like a broom."
msgstr ""

#: 1802
msgid "\"Greetings.\""
msgstr ""

#: 22700
msgid ""
"Mebbeth told me to take a strange black seed to one of the fruit merchants "
"at the Hive market and get some herbs from him. She said the market is a few "
"blocks south and east of her hut."
msgstr ""

#: 22703
msgid ""
"I met an old woman, Mebbeth, a midwife in Ragpicker's Square. She seems a "
"little addled... but so does everyone else in this berg."
msgstr ""

#: 22704
msgid ""
"Mebbeth offered to cure my wounds for free... it might be a good idea to "
"return to her every once in a while if I need healing. "
msgstr ""

#: 22705
msgid ""
"Mebbeth told me there's a gate that leads to Pharod's kip somewhere in the "
"Square. She said I should ask one of the other Collectors how I could find "
"it. "
msgstr ""

#: 22706
msgid ""
"Mebbeth told me Ravel's tale... she said she was a night hag on the Gray "
"Waste, but the dreariness of the place sowed discontent in Ravel's mind. "
"Ravel packed up her kip and came to Sigil in search of knowledge - but what "
"she learned she used against the city and the inhabitants themselves, acts "
"of such evil that Mebbeth could not describe them. Ravel was punished by the "
"Lady and sentenced to a maze, where the silence and quiet of the place may "
"have calmed her greedy heart. "
msgstr ""

#: 23159
msgid "Ignore the woman, explore the room."
msgstr ""

#: 23160
msgid ""
"The elderly woman turns and stares at you... and you notice the gray shades "
"blanketing her body extend to her features as well. Her hair is a wispy "
"gray, and her eyes are like chips of granite. She frowns when she sees you. "
"\"And who might ye be, hmmmn?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23161
msgid "\"I am a traveler.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23162
msgid "\"I don't really know who I am.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23163 23164
msgid "Lie: \"The name's Adahn. Who are you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23165 23188 23191
msgid "\"Sorry to disturb you. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23166
msgid ""
"Mebbeth turns as you enter and gives you a skeptical eye. \"Yer path brings "
"ye back here, does it, child...?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23167 23232
msgid "\"I found the fruit merchant in the market.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23168 23233
msgid ""
"\"I returned with those herbs you wanted... now maybe you can get this "
"damned bramble-patch off my wrist.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23169 23234 23624
msgid ""
"\"I brought your wash... I think Giscorl was a little heavy on the cleaning "
"ritual, though.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23170
msgid "\"Yes, I had some questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23171
msgid "\"Yes, I am in need of healing.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23172
msgid "\"I came to purchase some cures and charms from you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23173 23231 23629 23642
msgid "\"Could I rest here?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23174
msgid "\"No, I just came back to check on you. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23175
msgid "\"Is that so? An' where have ye traveled *from* then?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23176
msgid "\"To death's kingdom and back, I think.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23177
msgid "\"From the Mortuary through the Hive to here.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23178
msgid "\"Here and about... a number of places, really.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23179
msgid "\"It is of no importance. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23180
msgid ""
"The woman spits once... twice... three times, then makes a semi-circle over "
"her heart. \"'Ware what ye say, child -- and pray one of the Dead Powers "
"don't take offense at yer words.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23181 23187
msgid "\"I... see. Who are you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23182
msgid "\"I'll keep that in mind. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23183
msgid ""
"\"Hah! Mortuary pale-faces, all concerned with makin' sure th' deaders are "
"all in the jest the right places! Pah! Dusties n' fools - two words, same "
"meaning.\" The woman's features suddenly go blank, and her eyes roll to the "
"back of her head. "
msgstr ""

#: 23184
msgid "\"Are you all right?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23185
msgid "\"Uh... sorry to disturb you. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23186
msgid ""
"The woman starts mumbling, her tone mocking. \"Me am Dustie. Me want ta Die "
"cause this life fake.\" Her eyes snap back to front, and she snorts. "
"\"Dusties! No sense know-nothings!\" She points her finger at you. \"Ye run "
"outta this life, child, there's little or no place ta go.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23189
msgid ""
"\"Ahhh...\" She nods to herself. \"Yet in all yer wandering, ye've decided "
"to come to my door, have ye?\" She snorts. \"Blessed, am I.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23190
msgid "\"Who are you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23192
msgid ""
"\"So ye not know yerself, child?\" She squints, then points at your chest. "
"\"Hard ta piece together the man beneath all that tracery and scrawling "
"scars, is it?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23193
msgid "\"Maybe... who are you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23194 23293 23297 23301 23305 23425
msgid "\"I must take my leave. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23195
msgid ""
"With a sly cackle, she wags her eyebrows. \"Have ye not heard of Ol' Mebbeth "
"then, the midwife of the Square? Have ye not now?\" She narrows her eyes, "
"and her voice drops. \"Well, now ye have, fer *I* be Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23196
msgid "\"You're a midwife? What do you do?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23197
msgid ""
"\"I set bones right, drive the cough outta the sick, yank out squealing, "
"stubborn babes, mend cloaks or a rag or two, make cures and herbs and other "
"such.\" She squints at you, studying your scars. \"Be needin' a cure or "
"three, do ye then?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23198
msgid "\"Cures?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23199
msgid "\"No thanks. I must take my leave. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23200
msgid ""
"\"Aye, ye be needin' some cures ta lookatcha. D'ye want ta buy some, do "
"ye...?\" She glances at the scars covering your body again, then shrugs. "
"\"Too late ta be askin' for them, I think.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23201
msgid "\"Actually, I *could* use some healing...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23202
msgid "\"Actually, we *could* use some healing...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23203
msgid ""
"\"I don't need any cures now, but they might be useful later. Could I see "
"what you have?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23204
msgid ""
"\"Actually, I could just use a place to rest. Would you mind if I slept here?"
"\""
msgstr ""

#: 23205
msgid "\"Not at the moment. I had a question for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23206
msgid "\"I see. I must take my leave. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23207
msgid ""
"Mebbeth nods. \"Very well, then.\" She reaches for one of the dried herbs at "
"her belt, snaps it off at the stalk, then grinds it in her callused palms. "
"Small wisps of dust and pollen rise from her hands. She then mumbles to "
"herself, then blows the dust into the air..."
msgstr ""

#: 23208 23209
msgid "Take a deep breath."
msgstr ""

#: 23210
msgid ""
"The gray pollen swirls around the room, and you breath deeply... and less "
"than a moment later, you feel strangely refreshed. "
msgstr ""

#: 23211 23214
msgid "\"Thanks, Mebbeth. Before I go, I had some other questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23212 23215
msgid "\"Thank you, Mebbeth... I feel well again. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23213
msgid ""
"The gray pollen swirls around the room, blanketing you and your companions. "
"You breath deeply... and less than a moment later, you feel strangely "
"refreshed."
msgstr ""

#: 23216
msgid "\"Ye be wantin' anythin' else, child?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23217
msgid "\"Actually, yes... could I take another look at what you have?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23218
msgid "\"No, but I had some other questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23219
msgid "\"Not this day, Mebbeth... thanks. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23220
msgid ""
"\"I sell rags n' herbs n' cures n' charms n' mixes n' poultices n' all that "
"wash...\" She shrugs. \"Also, if ye find a queer item ye can't figure out, "
"bring it to Mebbeth... no promises, child, but mayhap I ken riddle out what "
"it is.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23221
msgid "\"I see. Can I see what you have to sell, then?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23222
msgid "\"Very well. I had some other questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23223 23250 23254 23258
msgid "\"That is all I wished to know. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23224
msgid "\"Go on n' ask, then.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23225
msgid "\"Do you know someone named Pharod?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23226
msgid "\"I'm missing a journal. Do you know where one could be found?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23227
msgid "\"Have you ever heard of someone named 'Ravel,' Mebbeth?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23228 23627 23638
msgid "\"I could use some healing...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23229 23639
msgid "\"What do you sell here, Mebbeth?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23230 23628 23641
msgid "\"Could I buy some cures from you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23235 23633
msgid ""
"\"I found Kossah-Jai. She doesn't have any ink, but another fishwife does... "
"thing is, I need something to hold the ink in.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23236 23635
msgid "\"Here's that ink you wanted.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23237
msgid "\"Are you a witch, Mebbeth?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23238
msgid "\"I want to learn the Art, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23239
msgid ""
"\"I'd like to switch my profession and concentrate on my mage studies, "
"Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23242 23630
msgid "\"No questions today. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23243
msgid ""
"\"Pharod?! That - that - pah!\" You watch as Mebbeth spits once... twice... "
"three times, then follows it by making a semi-circle over her heart. \"That "
"gull tird! Whatcha be wantin' with the likes of him?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23244
msgid "\"I need to find him. Do you know where he is?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23245
msgid "\"Never mind. I had some other questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23246
msgid "\"Nothing, never mind. I must take my leave. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23247
msgid ""
"\"He's not *in* Ragpicker's Square, that much I ken tell ye... ye need ta "
"find a way *under* the Square ta get ta that tird spider's kip.\" She spits "
"again. \"Even talkin' 'bout him leaves a foul taste, it does.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23248
msgid "\"He's under the Square?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23249 23253 23257
msgid "\"I see. I had some other questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23251
msgid ""
"She jabs her finger at the floor. \"Aye, he's buried beneath these piles of "
"trash, him and his boys, and a tough time ye'd have diggin' him out of his "
"nest.\" She shakes her head. \"Let be, let be, child.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23252
msgid "\"I need to find him. How do I get down there?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23256
msgid ""
"Mebbeth frowns, then sighs. \"Hear tell, Pharod's got a gate that leads to "
"his nest somewhere here in the Square...  it's jist a matter of findin' it. "
"Ye might want to ask some of the others, some who travel a bit more than Ol' "
"Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23259
msgid ""
"Mebbeth thinks. \"Haven't seen one. If it's in the Square -- which I doubt, "
"since folks don't traffic much with books and the like -- it's most likely "
"been sold or stolen. Was it somethin' important ta ye, then? A magic "
"thingee, all glowing and sparkling with magicks, eh? If so, ye might never "
"see it again.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23260
msgid "\"Maybe not. I had some other questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23261
msgid "\"I'm beginning to think I'll never see it again, either. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23262
msgid ""
"\"Pah!\" Mebbeth hisses and makes a semi-circle over her heart. \"What no-"
"sense-nothing ye goin' on about! Sayin' such a name in *me* presence!\" She "
"wags her finger at you. \"Evil, evil, sayin' such a thing brings evil to "
"one's door.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23263
msgid "\"What do you know about her?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23264 23268 23272 23276
msgid "\"Never mind, then. I had some other questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23265 23269 23273
msgid "\"Sorry, I didn't mean to offend you. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23266
msgid ""
"\"Ravel? Pah! Myths and scaredy-tales told ta childrens.\" Her voice drops, "
"as if warning you. \"Listen, child: NO Ravel was there, not at ALL... and "
"iffen there *was,* ye got no needin' to be rattlin' that Cage.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23267
msgid ""
"\"I need to know all you can tell me about her, Mebbeth. It's important.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23270
msgid ""
"Mebbeth frowns... she doesn't seem to want to meet your gaze. \"Bad "
"things... bad things in a name...\" She looks back at you. \"In Ravel's "
"queer hagheart, many shades of evil and badness, all a-crossin' and a-"
"twistin' like snakes. No more need be said, let be, let be!\""
msgstr ""

#: 23271
msgid "\"Do you know where she is, Mebbeth? I have to find her.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23274
msgid ""
"\"Where does one find a fairy's tale?! Mebbeth doesn't know!\" She hisses. "
"\"And *iffen* I did know the knowin', would I tell ye? Nay, ye'd try and dig "
"her up, and I can't have that on me mind, I can't...\" She seems "
"heartbroken. \"But, child... if ye need to know, if yer dead certain that "
"it's near to eatin' ye up inside, then... aye, then, I'll tell ye.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23275
msgid "\"Please... I have to find her, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23277
msgid "\"I don't need to know that badly. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23278
msgid ""
"Mebbeth suggested I go speak to one of the sages in the Civic Festhall in "
"the Clerk's Ward about how I might go about finding the entrance to Ravel's "
"maze."
msgstr ""

#: 23279
msgid ""
"\"Ravel...\" Mebbeth sighs. \"Ravel, cruel Ravel, lies in the Lady's "
"keepin', she does, in a prison, a maze... it's said she was put there so "
"long ago, so very long ago... but findin' it? Mebbeth knows not the way.\" "
"She sighs. \"Ask in the Festhall, mayhap, in the Clerk's Ward. One of the "
"graybeards there may have the dark of it...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23280
msgid ""
"\"Do you know anything else about Ravel... something you can tell me before "
"I seek her out?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23281
msgid ""
"\"Thanks... I'll go see what I can find out. I had some other questions, "
"first...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23282
msgid "\"I go speak to one of them then. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23283
msgid ""
"\"Child...\" Mebbeth speaks, but her voice sounds tired and broken. \"...if "
"ye seek evil in the Planes... ye need not travel far.\" She coughs. \"Witch "
"knows witch, power knows power, yet there is *none* who knows all Ravel's "
"branchings and twistings. Learn yer skills well, and keep yer lids open when "
"new sights don't be seeming right. Trust yerself, and do not be a-trustin' "
"her, hear?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23285
msgid "\"I will. Thanks, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23286
msgid ""
"Mebbeth sighs. \"I wish no ills upon others 'cept that one. Glad she's gone, "
"I am, and the Cage is better for it. Again, will I say this, child... let "
"the past rot where it lays. Let lie, let lie.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23287
msgid ""
"\"I will take your warning to heart. I had some other questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23289
msgid "\"I'm sorry, Mebbeth. I have to find Ravel. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23290
msgid ""
"\"Mayhap, if I were to begin a tale...\" Mebbeth speaks slowly, choosing her "
"words carefully. \"Mayhap the tale would begin with a gray *sister* who "
"lived upon the Planes, upon the fields of the Gray Wastes. The wastes were "
"such a quiet place, all quiet, and it was the silence that planted the seeds "
"of discontent in Ravel's heart.\" "
msgstr ""

#: 23291
msgid "\"Yes...?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23292 23296 23300 23304
msgid "\"I think I've heard enough. I had some other questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23294
msgid ""
"\"Always needin' the *why* and *how* and *what might be* of things, always "
"needin' to take one foot farther down the paths one should not travel.\" "
"Mebbeth sighs. \"And mayhap...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23295
msgid "\"And mayhap...?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23298
msgid ""
"\"And mayhap, Ravel, beautiful in her power and her cunning and her cruelty, "
"mayhap she traveled to this city, this Cage, that burns with too much bustle "
"and thought, because that was where people sought things just for the "
"*knowing* of them.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23299 23303
msgid "Listen."
msgstr ""

#: 23302
msgid ""
"\"Yet knowin' was not *enough* for one of Ravel's power, so many... many "
"were hurt, and the Cage, this city, it rattled with her needs and wants. "
"Such evils...\" She makes a semi-circle over her heart. \"Such were Ravel's "
"evils... it steals my words to think of them. She was cast out, into a "
"maze...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23306
msgid ""
"\"And mayhap that maze was quiet, too, like her small hut on the Gray "
"Wastes, and mayhap the silence and quiet had a chance to creep in to Ravel's "
"mind, now that they were not unwelcome, and cruel Ravel, for all her "
"branchings and twistings, was content again.\" Mebbeth sighs. \"And mayhap "
"that is how Ravel's tale ends. Who knows?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23307
msgid "\"Indeed. I had some other questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23308
msgid "\"Thank you for the tale, Mebbeth. I must take my leave. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23311
msgid ""
"\"Oh, come back to th' fold, have ye?\" Mebbeth chuckles dryly. \"Very well, "
"let's see what ye've forgotten and what ye've 'membered...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23312 23324 23325 23788
msgid "\"Very well...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23314
msgid ""
"Mebbeth taught me the Art, so I'm now focused on learning magic... I'll need "
"to find a thief or combat tutor if I want to switch back to one of the other "
"professions."
msgstr ""

#: 23316
msgid ""
"Mebbeth frowns, then nods. \"Ye've minded the teachings of the Art well "
"enough, ye have. Ye're focused on the wizardly arts now, ye are - no more "
"fightin' and thiefin' for ye unless ye talk to another who ken teach ye such "
"a thing.\" "
msgstr ""

#: 23317
msgid "\"Thanks, Mebbeth. I had some questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23318
msgid "\"I'll keep that in mind. Farewell, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23319
msgid ""
"Mebbeth shakes her head... a little sadly, it seems. \"I've taught ye all I "
"ken teach, child... the precious little I've left would not be of interest "
"to one such as ye. I'm proud of ye, I am. Ye've got the makings of a mighty "
"sorcerer, ye do.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23320
msgid "\"Thanks, Mebbeth. I had some other questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23321
msgid "\"I've had a good teacher. Farewell, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23322
msgid ""
"It looks like there's nothing more that Mebbeth can teach me in the Art. "
"I'll have to find some other tutors who have a wider range of magic."
msgstr ""

#: 23323
msgid ""
"Mebbeth scrutinizes you. \"Ye want to see what else I have to teach? Let's "
"see if ye've learned what I've already taught ye... and if ye have any room "
"in yer brain-box first, child...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23326
msgid ""
"Mebbeth said I need to gain a little more experience before she can teach me "
"anything more about the Art."
msgstr ""

#: 23327
msgid ""
"Mebbeth shakes her head. \"Ye need more time on th' forge, ye do, child. "
"Come back to me when ye've a little more o' the experience o' world in ye, "
"then we'll see about learnin' ye somethin' new.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23328
msgid "\"All right then. I had some questions for you before I go...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23330
msgid "\"I'll come back when I have more experience. Farewell, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23332
msgid ""
"Mebbeth nods her head. \"Aye, ye've grown, ye've learned, seems to me. "
"There's a bit more I ken teach ye, I can... another one o' me recipes...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23333
msgid "Spell 1: Intimidate"
msgstr ""

#: 23334
msgid "Spell 2: Friends"
msgstr ""

#: 23336
msgid "Spell 3: Pacify"
msgstr ""

#: 23338
msgid "Spell 4: Seizure"
msgstr ""

#: 23339
msgid "Spell 5: Blood Bridge"
msgstr ""

#: 23341
msgid "Spell 6: Irritation"
msgstr ""

#: 23343
msgid ""
"She nods. \"Of course, child. I have a mess of blankets in the corner that "
"would serve...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23346 23356 23358
msgid "\"That would be fine. Thank you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23360
msgid ""
"You awake, feeling refreshed. Mebbeth is puttering around the hut, but she "
"turns when she hears you stir. \"Awake, are ye? Ye slept like the dead...\" "
"She smiles. \"Do no dreams stir ye head?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23361
msgid "\"Uh... you know, I didn't have any dreams at all.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23362
msgid ""
"Mebbeth shrugs. \"Nothin' odd 'bout that. Most dreams are shy; they fly when "
"the sleeper's lids open.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23363
msgid ""
"\"No, but it doesn't feel like I forgot them... I don't think I dreamed "
"*anything.* It feels... wrong.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23364
msgid ""
"Mebbeth chews that over, then shrugs. \"Dreams ken make men great, but they "
"have laid low just as many. Mayhap yer better off without them nettlin' ye.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23365
msgid "\"Mayhap... but I don't think so.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23367
msgid ""
"When I was at Mebbeth's hut, I suddenly realized that I don't dream. It "
"doesn't feel like I'm forgetting my dreams... I don't think I'm dreaming at "
"*all.* It feels... wrong. I better look into it when I get the chance."
msgstr ""

#: 23369
msgid ""
"Mebbeth snorts. \"Well, dreams or no, I'm not one to change the nature of a "
"man. Have ye slept enough?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23413 23416
msgid "\"Yes, thanks... I had some other questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23414 23417
msgid "\"I think so. I better be on my way. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23415
msgid ""
"You awake, feeling refreshed. Mebbeth is puttering around the hut, but she "
"turns when she hears you stir. \"Awake, are ye? Did ye sleep well?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23418
msgid ""
"Mebbeth scrutinizes you. \"I say naught as to what I am and isn't, but "
"whatcha be wantin' ta know so fool bad for that ye hound an' ol' woman, "
"barkin' and sniffin' fer a juicy bit of gossip?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23419
msgid "\"I want to learn about magic. Could you teach me?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23420 23432 23450
msgid "\"No matter. I had some other questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23421
msgid "\"Never mind. I must take my leave. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23422
msgid ""
"Mebbeth laughs. \"Pah! I'm no teacher, no school-mistress all set up ta "
"teach like them in the big Festhall! There's others somewhere I'm sure "
"that'd spill the dark of it... ye'd be wastin' yer time with ol' Mebbeth, so "
"ye would.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23423
msgid "\"I don't agree. I think you'd have a lot to teach.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23424
msgid "\"No matter, then. I had some other questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23426
msgid ""
"Mebbeth looks at you intently. \"Oh, aye? *Why* do ye want to learn such "
"things?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23427
msgid "Truth: \"Because I just want to know.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23428
msgid "Truth: \"Because I may need it to solve the mystery of who I am.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23429
msgid "Truth: \"Because I need power.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23430
msgid ""
"Mebbeth scoffs. \"Not a child's grammar book this is, not a guvner's set of "
"laws... it's the *Art,* child. I'll teach ye, but ye've got ta keep a clear "
"head about ye.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23431
msgid "\"My reasons are my own.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23433
msgid "\"Never mind... I must take my leave. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23435 23439
msgid "\"I understand. Will you teach me?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23438
msgid ""
"After a moment, Mebbeth nods. \"The Art may help, it may not, and ye must "
"not rely on it ta solve all o' yer problems.\" She sighs. \"Child, it's most "
"like only going to add another chip to yer pile o' questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23442
msgid ""
"\"Pah! An ill-desire, fer the ladder of the Art will always remind ye that "
"ye there's another rung jist above ye, and there's a bunch of people and "
"things that'll be on it, too. There'll always be someone better, and they'll "
"learn *ye* if ye crave too much.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23443
msgid "\"I understand. Will you teach me anyway?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23446
msgid ""
"\"That so? Well, iffen yer reasons are yer own, then my *knowledge* is my "
"own. I won't teach one who hides hisself from the teacher... only evil comes "
"from such a path.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23447
msgid ""
"Truth: \"Very well, I want to learn the Art for the sake of knowing it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23448
msgid ""
"Truth: \"I want to learn the Art because I may need it to solve the mystery "
"of who I am.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23449
msgid "Truth: \"I want to learn the art because I need power.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23451
msgid "\"Never mind then. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23452
msgid ""
"\"Aye, well...\" She sniffs. \"If ye still want to learn, then I'll need "
"another task from ye. I forgot to tell ye to fetch one thing when ye left "
"last time, and it'll take ye back to the merchant square... look for the "
"cloth-seller, Giscorl. He has some rags of mine he was supposed to wash, and "
"long has it been since I first asked him to do it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23453 23556
msgid "\"I... see. Look, I had some questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23454 23558
msgid ""
"\"You could have *mentioned* that before I left... all right, I'll be back.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23455 23559
msgid "\"I'll go get it. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23456
msgid ""
"\"Pah!\" Mebbeth shakes her head. \"One should make songs rather than make "
"magick. Songs have more beauty. Magick's been made dull, common-place, "
"soiled by the mob of people that have tromped through it... hmpppph.\" She "
"squints at you. \"I'll teach ye... but first ye'll need to do some things "
"for *me,* ye hear?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23457
msgid "\"Like what?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23458
msgid ""
"\"My legs aren't good fer walkin' about Sigil, and there's errands I'd have "
"ye *run.* I need ye to fetch me some herbs from the market... it's spireward "
"-- easterly and southerly from here -- in the Hive market. Here's a sample..."
"\" She takes a black seed from her coat and flicks it to you. "
msgstr ""

#: 23459
msgid "Examine the seed."
msgstr ""

#: 23460
msgid ""
"You twist the black seed in your hand... as you do, you feel a small bite, "
"then a small drop of blood oozes from your thumb... there are tiny barbs on "
"the seed, like teeth. Mebbeth snorts. \"Careful with it... show it to one of "
"the fruit merchants at the market, they will know what herbs ye seek.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23461
msgid "\"All right. But I had some questions before I leave...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23462
msgid "\"Very well, then. I'll return when I have the herbs.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23463
msgid "\"Aye? Have ye gotten the herbs I wanted?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23464 23465
msgid ""
"\"Not yet, Mebbeth. He said he couldn't help me... that I'd have to find a "
"gardener.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23466
msgid "\"No, I had some other questions, actually...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23467
msgid "\"I'm still working on it. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23468
msgid ""
"Mebbeth sighs. \"Nothin' to be done, I s'pose.\" She grunts. \"Well, no "
"matter, child, no matter. I'll see if I ken coax one of me old seeds to "
"grow, though it'll take time. I think I still have one or two left...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23469
msgid "\"All right then...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23471
msgid ""
"Mebbeth wants me to fetch her wash from the cloth-seller in the market, a "
"fellow named Giscorl. I wish she'd remembered it before I went looking for "
"those herbs of hers..."
msgstr ""

#: 23472
msgid ""
"Mebbeth grunts. \"Lay-abouts... in the olden days, people gave ingredients, "
"not excuses...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23473
msgid "\"So what should be done?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23474
msgid "\"I suppose so. Anyway, I had some questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23475
msgid "\"Well, I'll hunt around some more. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23476
msgid "Mebbeth sighs. \"Look for a gardener, I s'pose.\" She chews her lip."
msgstr ""

#: 23477
msgid "\"Where?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23478
msgid "\"Very well then. Look, I had some questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23479
msgid "\"I'll hunt around some more, then. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23480
msgid ""
"Mebbeth frowns. \"I haven't been out of this hut in many cycles, child. I "
"don't know where one might find a gardener... but if ye want to learn the "
"Art, ye'll have to learn to be persistent, so *look.* There must be one "
"somewhere in the Hive.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23481
msgid "\"Very well... but before I go, I had some questions for you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23482
msgid "\"I'll go look for one, then.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23483
msgid "\"Maybe Mourns-for-Trees can help me... Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23484
msgid ""
"\"Is that so?\" Mebbeth glances at the barbs that surround your wrist. \"If "
"so, *think* it off, then.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23485
msgid "Do so."
msgstr ""

#: 23486
msgid ""
"Creaking and snapping, the black-barbed branches unravel themselves from "
"your wrist and form into a tangled ball of brush and twigs; it looks like a "
"nest of dead black snakes. Mebbeth snorts. \"Think it into a picture frame "
"or somesuch, somethin' with more structure and less angles.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23487
msgid ""
"Mebbeth wants me to fetch her wash from the cloth-seller in the market, a "
"fellow named Giscorl. I wish she'd remembered it before I went looking for "
"those herbs of hers... "
msgstr ""

#: 23488
msgid "Try and imagine the barbed-ball into a picture frame."
msgstr ""

#: 23489 23503
msgid "Imagine the barbed-ball into a picture frame."
msgstr ""

#: 23490 23505
msgid "Concentrate on the barbed-ball, then imagine it as a picture frame."
msgstr ""

#: 23535
msgid ""
"You focus for a moment, and try to picture a frame in your mind... there is "
"a creaking and snapping from the ball, and you open your eyes: it has warped "
"itself into a bizarre cube with its barbs all facing outwards. Anyone who "
"picked it up would slice their hands to ribbons."
msgstr ""

#: 23536 23738
msgid "\"Uh...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23538
msgid "Mebbeth snorts. \"Maybe ye'd better try again.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23540
msgid "Take a breath, focus, then try again."
msgstr ""

#: 23541
msgid ""
"The branched ball creaks, the twigs bending and twisting until the branches "
"have bent themselves into a crude picture frame, two handspans on a side."
msgstr ""

#: 23542 23549 23551
msgid "\"How's that?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23544
msgid ""
"Mebbeth stares at the frame critically for a moment, then nods. \"Square "
"enough.\" She picks up the frame and scrutinizes it. \"It'll do... it'll do."
"\""
msgstr ""

#: 23546 23553
msgid "\"Is that all you wanted it for?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23548
msgid ""
"The branched ball creaks, the twigs bending and twisting until the branches "
"have bent themselves into a small picture frame, two handspans on a side. "
"Almost unconsciously, you imagine-shape the barbs to the back of the frame "
"so it can be hung from the wall easily."
msgstr ""

#: 23550
msgid ""
"The branched ball creaks, the twigs bending and twisting until the branches "
"have bent themselves into a small picture frame, two handspans on a side. "
"Almost unconsciously, you imagine-shape the barbs to the back of the frame "
"so it can be hung from the wall easily... and, as an afterthought, you move "
"the remaining barbed to the inside of the frame so it can be picked up by "
"the edges."
msgstr ""

#: 23552
msgid ""
"Mebbeth stares at the frame for a moment, then cackles. \"Ha! Square enough, "
"it is! Good work, child, good work.\" She picks up the frame and scrutinizes "
"it. \"This'll do nicely.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23554
msgid ""
"\"Aye, well, this is enough...\" She sniffs. \"Aye, but there was one thing "
"I forgot to tell ye to fetch when ye left last time, and it'll take ye back "
"to the merchant square it will... look for the cloth-seller, Giscorl. He has "
"some rags of mine that he was supposed to wash, and long has it been since I "
"first asked him to do it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23561
msgid ""
"She takes the stacks of starched-green rags from you, and she examines them "
"critically. \"At least they won't tear.\" She sighs. \"Or bend.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23562
msgid ""
"\"What was with that cloth-merchant, Giscorl? His hands were all scarred. "
"and he seemed... slow.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23563
msgid ""
"Mebbeth is still turning the cloth over in her hands, tapping it with her "
"finger. \"Well, child, sometimes one burns with the Art, and other times, "
"the Art burns ye.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23564
msgid "\"Is that what happened to him?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23565
msgid ""
"Mebbeth clicks her tongue. \"Mayhap. There's somes for who usin' the Art is "
"like breathing. They strolls about with pointy hats and stinkweed pipes... "
"then there's hedge-wizards n' plane-touched gypsies n' fortune-casters n' "
"half-seers n' midwives who flicker with the Art... them have a harder time "
"of it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23567
msgid "\"And Giscorl was one of them?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23568
msgid ""
"Mebbeth nods. \"Aye... so to speak. In some ways, he's no different now than "
"he was. Addicted to habit and ritual, he was.\" She sets down the stiff "
"rags; they *clunk* as she places them on the floor. \"Aye, now, there's one "
"last thing I need from ye, child...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23569
msgid "\"This better not involve me going back to the market, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23570
msgid "\"Of course. What do you need?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23571
msgid ""
"\"Oh? And iffen it does, child?!\" Mebbeth draws herself up, and she glares "
"at you. Even at full height, her head barely crests your shoulders. "
msgstr ""

#: 23572
msgid ""
"\"Mebbeth, it's a waste of time to keep traveling to the market for all "
"these things, especially when you could have taken a moment and thought "
"about everything you needed instead of sending me on the same errand *three* "
"times.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23574
msgid ""
"\"All's I'm saying is that if you can't keep your head straight about what "
"you need from the market, I doubt you can teach me much about magic.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23575
msgid "\"Never mind. What do you need?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23577
msgid ""
"Mebbeth puffs up, her face turning turnip-red. \"Oh, aye? Is that yer "
"feelin's on the matter, is it? If so, then leave! I'll tell ye, I won't be a-"
"wastin' my time tryin' to shine light in that mule-head o' yers!\""
msgstr ""

#: 23578
msgid ""
"\"No, I'll do the errands... just tell me: is there anything else you need "
"me to pick up while I'm there?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23580
msgid "\"All right, all right. I spoke in haste. What do you need?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23581
msgid "\"Fine, I'm leaving. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23583
msgid ""
"\"Only this: I need some inks fer scribin' some ingredients in one of me "
"cookery books. I'll need ye to fetch some from one of the merchants -- "
"Kossah-Jai, be her name.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23584
msgid ""
"\"Very well. I'll go see if I can find her, but I had some questions first..."
"\""
msgstr ""

#: 23585
msgid "\"All right, then... I'm off. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23587
msgid ""
"Mebbeth needs me to run yet *another* damnable errand for her... it's back "
"to the market again to fetch some ink. She said to speak to a woman named "
"Kossah-Jai in the market square. She's probably the only merchant I "
"*haven't* spoken to yet."
msgstr ""

#: 23589
msgid ""
"\"Can't ye get a cup, or a bowl, or a tankard or something from one of the "
"other merchants?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23590
msgid ""
"\"I could. I'll ask one of the other merchants, but I had some other "
"questions for you first...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23592
msgid "\"I suppose I could... oh, well, I'm off. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23595
msgid ""
"Mebbeth takes the tankard of ink from you, then sniffs it. \"Prime ink, "
"fresh it is, aye...\" She nods at you. \"Ye've done well, child. All I've "
"asked. Now, I ask ye again: after all ye've seen, do ye still want to learn "
"the art?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23596
msgid "\"After all I've seen? What do you mean?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23597
msgid "\"Yes, I do.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23598 23600
msgid ""
"\"Yes. After all, the guiding goal of your errands was to test my "
"persistence, was it not?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23601
msgid "\"No, I don't think the Art is for me. Farewell, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23604
msgid "Mebbeth smiles, then nods. \"Yes... mayhap, child, mayhap.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23605
msgid ""
"\"And that's not all; you knew who I had to see to accomplish each errand, "
"didn't you?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23607
msgid "\"Very well. I still want to learn the Art.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23609
msgid ""
"Mebbeth nods again, slower this time. \"Mayhap, child, mayhap... iffen so, "
"what did yer senses tell ye about them?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23611
msgid ""
"\"Mourns-for-Trees showed me that my beliefs affect the world around me, "
"Giscorl taught me that ritual is a wasted effort if the purpose of the "
"ritual is ignored, Meir'am taught me that no matter how much I think I know, "
"there is still much I can learn from another's eyes.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23612
msgid ""
"Mebbeth is silent for a moment, then she walks slowly over to you and "
"touches you on the cheek. \"Oh, child...\" She sighs. \"Ye will be a master "
"sorcerer one day, ye will. Ye have the knowin' of it, yet... ye've come to "
"Ol' Mebbeth for help, ye have. What could a midwife teach such a one?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23613
msgid "\"Much, Mebbeth. I want to learn all you have to teach.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23614
msgid "\"From all ye've seen... have ye learned anythin'?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23615
msgid ""
"\"I learned I must be willing to put up with a lot of running around if I "
"want to get anything out of you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23616
msgid ""
"\"Well, some things. Not anything I could really comment on... except that I "
"want to learn the Art.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23619
msgid ""
"Mebbeth laughs. \"And so it is with the Art, child, so it is with the Art. "
"Many errands will ye run in its name, some seemin' to have no sense about "
"them. Knowin' that, do ye still want to learn?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23621 23648
msgid "\"Yes.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23623
msgid ""
"Mebbeth seems lost in twisting the black-branched picture frame you made for "
"her... she is squaring the edges and snapping off some of the barbed seeds "
"on the branches. She suddenly notices you and sets down the frame. \"Aye, "
"child?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23626 23636
msgid "\"I had some questions for you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23632
msgid ""
"Mebbeth is tugging at the mass of greenish-lime starched rags you brought "
"from Giscorl... she seems to be purposely fraying the edges, as if to peel "
"them apart somehow. When she hears you approach, she turns. \"Aye, child?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23643
msgid "\"Nothing. Just checking up on you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23644
msgid ""
"\"So ye'll walk the path then...\" Mebbeth pauses. \"Well, first things "
"firstly: jest havin' the knack for the Art isn't enough. Ye need some means "
"of givin' it focus: usually 'spells.' The spells are usually in a book. So "
"the Art demands ye have a spell book or its like a-fore ye ken cast spells. "
"Ken ye read?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23647
msgid "\"I don't know.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23649
msgid ""
"\"Then let's test it, ken ye read this?\" Mebbeth draws forth a small "
"tattered card... it looks like a recipe. "
msgstr ""

#: 23651 23652
msgid "Examine the recipe."
msgstr ""

#: 23654
msgid ""
"The writing on the recipe swims before your eyes, each symbol twisting out "
"of focus whenever you try and read it. Almost instinctively, you relax your "
"eyes, allowing them to take in the page all at once... and the symbols "
"suddenly bleed together: the recipe lists measurements, ingredients... it "
"appears to be some minor divination."
msgstr ""

#: 23674 23685
msgid ""
"\"This is a minor divination, isn't it? It looks like it's a spell that "
"allows the user to see the 'nature' of an item... to see whether it's "
"enchanted or not.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23675
msgid ""
"\"Here, ken ye read this?\" Mebbeth draws forth a small tattered card... it "
"looks like a recipe. Strangely enough, the writing on the recipe swims "
"before your eyes, each symbol twisting out of focus whenever you try and "
"read it. "
msgstr ""

#: 23676
msgid "Study the symbols, see if you can decipher them."
msgstr ""

#: 23677 23680 23683
msgid "\"I give up, Mebbeth... what does this writing mean?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23678
msgid ""
"You study the symbols intently. No matter how hard you concentrate, however, "
"the writing on the recipe seems to flow out of focus, bending and twisting "
"like a nest of snakes. It makes your eyes hurt just trying to follow their "
"movements. "
msgstr ""

#: 23679 23682
msgid "Keep studying the symbols, try and puzzle out their meaning. "
msgstr ""

#: 23681
msgid ""
"You keep studying the symbols for a few more minutes, Mebbeth silently "
"watching you. "
msgstr ""

#: 23684
msgid ""
"As you are about to give up and turn away, you relax your eyes and take in "
"the page all at once... as you do, the symbols suddenly bleed together: the "
"recipe lists measurements, ingredients: it appears to be some sort of minor "
"divination."
msgstr ""

#: 23686
msgid ""
"Mebbeth's eyes widen. \"Who are ye to test Ol' Mebbeth so?! Are ye some "
"fiend?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23687
msgid "\"What's wrong?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23688
msgid "\"No... well, not to my knowledge. What's wrong?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23689
msgid ""
"\"Some have called me so, but not in my presence. Is there something wrong?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23690
msgid ""
"Mebbeth gave me a test... a small recipe, a minor illusion, written in the "
"language of the Art. I was able to decipher its meaning with no training. I "
"must have learned how to read magic at some point in the past."
msgstr ""

#: 23691
msgid ""
"\"Well... not expectin' it, was I...\" She nods at the recipe, then plucks "
"it out of your hand. \"What ye see, it's written in the language of the *Art."
"* If ye're not a mageling yet, it should be all-a-swirl-jumble of mish-mash."
"\" She snaps her finger. \"Yet, clear as crystal, ye pluck the sense of it "
"right up. Mayhap ye tell Ol' Mebbeth why that is?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23692
msgid "\"I don't really know... I just *knew* what it said.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23693
msgid ""
"\"I think I may have known once, but forgot... seeing the symbols just "
"jarred my memory.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23694
msgid ""
"\"Or else a natural gift, ye may have... no matter, no matter, ye've just "
"shaved seasons off of yer learning, ye have.\" Mebbeth *harumphs.* \"An I'd "
"been lookin' fer someone to handle the chores around here, I had...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23695
msgid "\"Maybe it's just as well, then.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23696
msgid ""
"\"If you need help with anything around here, you can still ask... it's the "
"least I can do in exchange for you teaching me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23697
msgid ""
"\"Pah! And to think I took ye in...\" She frowns. \"Well, ye ken read spells "
"well enough, but spells are no good to ye without a book to put them in...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23698 23699 23701 23702
msgid "\"Do you have one?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23700
msgid ""
"\"No, no, don't worry yerself about that...\" She frowns. \"Well, ye ken "
"read spells well enough, but spells are no good to ye without a book to put "
"them in...\" "
msgstr ""

#: 23703
msgid ""
"Mebbeth glances around the hut, and then she catches sight of the black-"
"barbed picture frame you made. She picks it up carefully and studies it. "
"\"This'll do.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23704 23706
msgid "\"That thing? It's just a frame.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23705
msgid ""
"Mebbeth glances around the hut, and then she catches sight of a black-barbed "
"picture frame on one of the walls. She pulls it off the wall carefully and "
"studies it. \"This'll do.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23707
msgid ""
"\"Ah, but so are ye, child...\" Still holding the frame, she picks up one of "
"the starched rags you got from Giscorl. With a yank, she pulls off the "
"greenish starched-surface film; it flutters in the air like a wispy bit of "
"cloth. \"Whatever Giscorl uses in the wash, it works better than curing, "
"stretchin' and stonin' does on a normal rag. Can't afford parchment, I "
"can't...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23708
msgid "\"Parchment...?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23709
msgid ""
"She takes the starchy film and pulls it over the black-barbed frame, "
"latching the rag's edges onto the hooks around the frame until it looks like "
"a small greenish-black painter's canvas. \"It's missin' something...\" "
msgstr ""

#: 23710
msgid "\"Well, it needs something painted on it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23711
msgid ""
"She nods. \"Aye, or written on it...\" She takes the tankard of ink you've "
"given her and sets it down next to her. She dips one of her fingernails into "
"the tankard, then draws it out, mumbling to herself. She begins to scratch "
"symbols onto the frame, one by one, still mumbling to herself."
msgstr ""

#: 23712
msgid "Wait..."
msgstr ""

#: 23713
msgid ""
"\"All's done.\" Mebbeth stands, drying her ink-stained fingernail on her "
"robe. She tilts her head, regarding the strange, framed page in front of "
"her. \"A page fer yer spell book, it is.\" She indicates you should pick it "
"up."
msgstr ""

#: 23714
msgid "Take it..."
msgstr ""

#: 23715
msgid ""
"\"Inside yer spell book are yer recipes... yer 'spells'... if you will. As "
"long as they sit in the book, though, they're jist words.\" She taps her "
"head. \"The Art demands ye pluck the magick out of the book and put them in "
"yer attic... yer head, a-fore ye ken tap their power.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23716
msgid "\"Go on...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23717 23721 23725 23728 23734 23739 23742 23745 23749 23752
msgid "\"I think I understand the basics, Mebbeth. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23718
msgid ""
"\"Ye put them in yer attic by studyin' 'em, *memorizing* them. Ye usually "
"need ta rest first a-fore ye ken do this, though. Any questions?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23719
msgid "\"No, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23720
msgid "\"Yes... explain that again.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23722
msgid ""
"\"Oh, no questions, eh? Well now, ye *should* have questions! Ye know all's "
"about how to memorize spells do ye? Yer a sharp one! Ye sure don't need any "
"more of Mebbeth's words all-a-gobblin' up yer precious time... yer a master "
"sorcerer already!\""
msgstr ""

#: 23723
msgid ""
"\"Forgive me, Mebbeth. I *meant* no questions on what you'd said. Please "
"explain how to memorize spells.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23724
msgid "\"Your attitude is trying my patience, Mebbeth...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23726
msgid ""
"\"Hmmph. All right then. Here's the dark of how ye memorize the spells: Pick "
"the spells ye want to stick in yer head from yer spell book *a-fore* ye goes "
"to sleep. When ye wake in the morn, they'll be buzzin' in yer head like "
"flies, ready ta be let out.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23727
msgid "\"How many spells can I cast?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23729
msgid ""
"\"Aye, I'll be any way I like with ye, child, so's I will, and ye'll pay "
"attention right quick if ye wish to know the dark of the Art!\""
msgstr ""

#: 23730
msgid "\"Forgive me, Mebbeth. Please explain how to memorize spells.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23731
msgid "\"If you're *done* with the lecture, then continue.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23732
msgid ""
"\"Ye ken cast only one, mayhap two spells a-fore needin' to rest again... as "
"a tiny flitting mageling, there isn't much room in yer attic. So's use yer "
"spells wisely until ye get wiser in the art. As yer power increases, ye'll "
"get more room in yer attic for spells.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23733
msgid "\"All right... go on...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23735
msgid ""
"\"Ye ken only cast spells ye've memorized. So if ye want to use the Art to "
"say, Mend somethin' twice, ye need to memorize the spell... how many times?"
"\" "
msgstr ""

#: 23736
msgid "\"Once.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23737
msgid "\"Twice.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23740
msgid ""
"\"Twice! To cast a spell *twice,* ye need to memorize the spell *twice.*\""
msgstr ""

#: 23741
msgid "\"Got it. How can I get more spells?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23743
msgid "Mebbeth nods. \"Aye, twice, right enough.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23744
msgid "\"How can I get more spells?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23746
msgid ""
"Mebbeth taught me the fundamentals of the Art. She says that before I rest, "
"I'll need to pick what spells I want to memorize by going to my spell book "
"and choosing them. If I want to be able to cast a spell multiple times, I'll "
"have to memorize the spell multiple times.  Whenever I rest, I'll awake the "
"next morning with the spells in my memory, ready to be cast. She said I'll "
"only be able to cast a small number of spells each day until I become more "
"proficient in their use. I might be able to find other teachers around Sigil "
"who can teach me to cast spells as well."
msgstr ""

#: 23747
msgid ""
"Mebbeth shrugs. \"Keep yer eyes and ears out for learnin' - even common "
"folks might have some minor magicks to teach. There's also scrolls, recipes, "
"books and even some stranger items that have spells inscribed on 'em. If ye "
"find one, just examine it close and copy it into yer book if ye want it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23748
msgid "\"Got it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23750
msgid ""
"\"I ken also show ye more spells if ye return, especially when ye've a "
"little more o' the planes in ye.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23751
msgid "\"I'd appreciate it. Thanks.\" "
msgstr ""

#: 23753
msgid ""
"\"A-fore ye go, child, ye'll need some magicks for ye to whet yer appetite..."
"\" Mebbeth rummages in her robe, then pulls forth three small recipes, which "
"she passes to you. \"Ye should copy these into yer book, so they ken go into "
"yer attic as soon as possible...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23754
msgid "\"Thanks, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23755
msgid ""
"\"All right child -- don't tarry here any longer. One such as ye has other "
"ways to spend one's time rather than hang around Ol' Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23756
msgid "\"Now, come on, Mebbeth, you're not old.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23757
msgid "\"You're not so old.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23758
msgid "\"Aye, that be the truth. I've spent too much time here already.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23759
msgid ""
"Mebbeth gave me three 'recipes' which she said I should copy into my spell "
"book. She told me I should examine them in my inventory, then 'copy' them "
"into my spell book."
msgstr ""

#: 23760
msgid ""
"\"Pah, ye flatterer! Yer tongue is so lined with silver it'd shame a "
"Baatezu! Get ye hince!\""
msgstr ""

#: 23761
msgid "\"Thanks for everything, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23762
msgid "\"Farewell, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23763
msgid ""
"\"Ye've got the temperment ta be one of those high-saddled sorcerors.\" "
"Mebbeth snorts. \"Still... I wish ye well, child. I wish ye well.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23764 23766 23807
msgid "\"Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23765
msgid ""
"\"Pah! Ye ken thank me by not playin' the addle-cove with what've learned. "
"The Art's damned many a fool who sought to bend it in ways the Art weren't "
"meant to bend. Now get along with ye!\""
msgstr ""

#: 23767
msgid ""
"As you enter, Mebbeth looks up, her face ashen... she looks ill. As you "
"watch, creases spread across the folds her face like cracks, and her gray "
"eyes flicker, as if having trouble focusing on you. "
msgstr ""

#: 23768
msgid "\"I thought you might still be here, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23769
msgid "\"You aren't dead, yet, 'Mebbeth?'\""
msgstr ""

#: 23770 23772 23774
msgid "\"Mebbeth... did you *know* you were Ravel?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23771
msgid ""
"\"Aye...\" She smiles weakly, and her voice is scratchy, as if trying to "
"force its way past layers of dust. When she speaks, it is like an echo. \"I "
"have... a little longer...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23773
msgid "\"Nay...\" She smiles weakly. \"I have... a little longer...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23775
msgid ""
"She takes a deep breath... her words come slowly, her voice rattling in her "
"throat. \"Mayhap... Mebbeth has forgotten herself many times over... I have "
"dreamed that I was someone else...\" Each word is heavier than the last, as "
"if centuries of weight are pressing down on them. Her body seems to shift "
"slightly, as if wanting to *relax,* let go. "
msgstr ""

#: 23776
msgid "\"How could you not know who you are?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23777
msgid ""
"\"How is it *ye* do not know yerself?\" Mebbeth licks her lips. \"Many "
"things... even bits of the self... they fall through memory's cracks, "
"shadows of things forgotten, these memory thing-pieces, maybe bad... maybe "
"good.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23778
msgid ""
"\"But why Mebbeth? Why the disguise when you could have been Ravel again?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23779
msgid ""
"\"Here, in this place, all I did was the mendin' of things and bodies, "
"settin' bones, deliverin' babes... in all these things, I was content.\" She "
"sighs. \"As for being that *other,* that Ravel...\" She licks her lips "
"again. \"I think... ye take for granted what a comfort it would be, oft "
"times, to misplace a memory or two.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23780
msgid "\"I wasn't sure if you would be here, Mebbeth, after what happened...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23781
msgid ""
"Mebbeth nods - every movement is pained. \"Aye, my precious one...\" She "
"winces as she takes a breath. \"Seeing ye here... it is like an echo. Little "
"time remains... the threads, these Ravels... they are unraveling as we speak."
"\" "
msgstr ""

#: 23782
msgid "\"Are you in pain?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23783
msgid ""
"She nods. \"Yes... yet it is the irony which hurts the most...\" She gives a "
"sickly smile. \"An act of kindness, thrice repaid... it is the way of the "
"Planes that my few acts of kindness should be the death of me.\" She laughs "
"softly. \"Yet I have no regrets...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23784
msgid ""
"\"I have questions, Mebbeth. I need to know who *did* this to you. Can you "
"t--\""
msgstr ""

#: 23785
msgid ""
"She holds up her hand to silence you. \"Precious man... I would have ye hear "
"me, this last time...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23786
msgid "\"Mebbeth, there's not much *time*...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23792
msgid ""
"\"Precious man...\" She sighs. \"All's I wished to do was set the Lady free "
"of her Cage... for ye, all's I wished for ye was to *live*... and for me "
"daughter, I...\" She sighs. \"There is a saying on the Planes... that a "
"hag's kindness is crueler... than her hate, and poisons all it touches...\""
msgstr ""

#: 23793 23795
msgid "\"I think we've seen the truth of that.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23794 23796
msgid ""
"\"I'm sorry things turned out as it did. If I could have saved you, I --\""
msgstr ""

#: 23797
msgid ""
"She smiles slightly. \"I do not regret what has happened, my precious...\" "
"Her smile fades. \"Nor should ye.\" Her eyes film over, and her gaze loses "
"focus. \"Ah... I... ken stay here... no longer.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23798
msgid "\"Good riddance, Ravel. May a darker place than this be your home.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23799
msgid "\"Farewell, Ravel.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23800
msgid ""
"\"I am dying now...\" She blinks her rheumy eyes. \"My end... it's traveling "
"from all of time's directions, all of Ravel's threads are unraveling...\" "
"She coughs. \"Yet...\" Her gray eyes lock upon you. \"Mayhap not all is "
"lost... one of my black-barbed seeds from the maze... did ye bring one with "
"ye?\""
msgstr ""

#: 23801
msgid "\"Yes. Here.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23802
msgid "\"I have it, but I will not give it to you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23803
msgid ""
"\"Ah...\" She takes the seed gingerly, and she slips it into her graying "
"locks. \"So the Unity-of-Rings is served...\" With a flickering glance, she "
"raises her hand and beckons you to come closer."
msgstr ""

#: 23804
msgid "Step close to her, kneel down. "
msgstr ""

#: 23805
msgid ""
"\"No... no matter what guise you wear, you are Ravel, and I do not trust "
"you. Mebbeth I mourn. You I do not.\""
msgstr ""

#: 23806
msgid ""
"She nods, looks like she is about to say something, then smiles and closes "
"her eyes. "
msgstr ""

#: 23809
msgid ""
"She whispers something softly under her breath, then clasps your head in her "
"hands and places a paper-thin kiss upon your forehead. You close your eyes "
"as her lips touch your skin... "
msgstr ""

#: 23810
msgid "\"May the Planes receive you kindly, Mebbeth.\""
msgstr ""

#: 62022
msgid ""
"\"I was a mage, once, but have turned from the path of the Art. I'd like to "
"become one again.\""
msgstr ""

#: 64215
msgid "\"Mebbeth, are you all right?\""
msgstr ""

#: 64216
msgid ""
"\"Mebbeth... your voice... you're speaking in *Ravel's* voice. Who *are* "
"you?!\""
msgstr ""

#: 66278
msgid ""
"\"Wait... there's more...\" Mebbeth fishes a tiny bundle of black cloth from "
"her apron and unrolls it, producing a pair of amber earrings. \"These'll "
"protect ye on yer travels, child... I no longer wear them meself, so go "
"ahead an' take them.\""
msgstr ""

#: 66279
msgid "\"Thanks again...\""
msgstr ""
